mec@shout.net said:
>  Please guys, focus your opinions as "this is why I like my favorite
> look and feel for xconfig",
I once saw a research OS with a configuration utility based on xconfig.
It showed the dependencies for each config option next to them, sort of like 
LEDs so you could see the deps, and even click on them to change them.
For example...
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 | FAT filesystem                                             |
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 | VFAT filesystem                  O FAT                     |
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 | MSDOS filesystem                 O FAT                     |
 --------------------------------------------------------------
 | UMSDOS filesystem                O MSDOS   O EXPERIMENTAL  |
 --------------------------------------------------------------
